dma: sun4i: fix DDMA completion IRQ bit mapping on suniv (4 NDMA channels)

The IRQ enable/pending register packs NDMA channel events in the low 16 bits and
DDMA events in the high 16 bits (2 bits/channel), regardless of how many NDMA
channels the SoC implements. set_pchan_interrupt() and the irq handler assumed a
contiguous layout (bit = pchan_index * 2), which is only correct when there are 8
NDMA channels (A10): there DDMA pchan 8 -> bit 16.

On suniv (F1C100s/F1C200s) there are only 4 NDMA channels, so the first DDMA
pchan is index 4 and the driver used bit 8 -- but the hardware still raises the
DDMA completion at bit 16. The enable bit (9) and the hardware's pending bit (17)
never matched, so DDMA end-interrupts were masked and never serviced: DDMA
transfers completed into SDRAM but their dmaengine callbacks never ran. NDMA was
unaffected (ch0 = bit 0/1 either way), which is why SPI DMA worked but the USB
DDMA (used by the MUSB sunxi_dma backend) hung every transfer.

Map DDMA pchans to the high 16 bits explicitly in both the enable path and the
handler's reverse lookup. A10 behaviour is unchanged (ndma=8 -> DDMA still at
bit 16).

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>

--- a/drivers/dma/sun4i-dma.c
+++ b/drivers/dma/sun4i-dma.c
@@ -377,21 +377,36 @@
 {
 	u32 reg;
 	int pchan_number = pchan - priv->pchans;
+	int irq_bit;
 	unsigned long flags;
 
+	/*
+	 * The IRQ enable/pending register keeps NDMA events in the low 16 bits
+	 * and DDMA events in the high 16 bits, independent of how many NDMA
+	 * channels the SoC has. On the A10 (8 NDMA channels) a DDMA pchan index
+	 * already lands at bit 16+, but on suniv (only 4 NDMA channels) it does
+	 * not, so map DDMA pchans to the high half explicitly. Without this the
+	 * suniv DDMA completion IRQ (hw bit 16+) is enabled at the wrong bit and
+	 * never handled, so DDMA transfers finish in SDRAM but never call back.
+	 */
+	if (pchan_number < priv->cfg->ndma_nr_max_channels)
+		irq_bit = pchan_number * 2;
+	else
+		irq_bit = 16 + (pchan_number - priv->cfg->ndma_nr_max_channels) * 2;
+
 	spin_lock_irqsave(&priv->lock, flags);
 
 	reg = readl_relaxed(priv->base + SUN4I_DMA_IRQ_ENABLE_REG);
 
 	if (half)
-		reg |= BIT(pchan_number * 2);
+		reg |= BIT(irq_bit);
 	else
-		reg &= ~BIT(pchan_number * 2);
+		reg &= ~BIT(irq_bit);
 
 	if (end)
-		reg |= BIT(pchan_number * 2 + 1);
+		reg |= BIT(irq_bit + 1);
 	else
-		reg &= ~BIT(pchan_number * 2 + 1);
+		reg &= ~BIT(irq_bit + 1);
 
 	writel_relaxed(reg, priv->base + SUN4I_DMA_IRQ_ENABLE_REG);
 
@@ -1132,7 +1147,13 @@
 	free_room = 0;
 
 	for_each_set_bit(bit, &pendirq, 32) {
-		pchan = &pchans[bit >> 1];
+		/* Inverse of the NDMA-low / DDMA-high(16+) split in
+		 * set_pchan_interrupt(): map the register bit back to a pchan.
+		 */
+		int pchan_idx = (bit < 16) ? (bit >> 1) :
+			priv->cfg->ndma_nr_max_channels + ((bit - 16) >> 1);
+
+		pchan = &pchans[pchan_idx];
 		vchan = pchan->vchan;
 		if (!vchan) /* a terminated channel may still interrupt */
 			continue;
